clientTexts.value: Event rewards and gifts may be sent to your mailbox, check it regularly!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_002
clientTexts.value: Your bag contains all the items and gear you are carrying around, expand it to bring more items during your adventure.

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_003
clientTexts.value: Tap the map to see all the NPC, monsters and portals in your area and move there automatically.

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_004
clientTexts.value: Compete the Daily Quests to earn EXP and Penya, if you finish the 10 dailies you will earn extra rewards.

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_005
clientTexts.value: Visit Flarine to access your Storage and deposit items and Penya when your bag is full, or reach VIP 3 to access the Storage remotely!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_006
clientTexts.value: You can buy items sold by other players at the Auction House, or you may sell your own items and Penya.

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_009
clientTexts.value: You can only enter Mokomoci's Hill three times a day, but it will give you a lot of EXP. If you are strong enough to kill all the Masquerpets, you can receive a special reward!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_010
clientTexts.value: Fight the Hyenas stealing all the Penya in Saint Dock once a day. The more you kill, the richer you will get!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_011
clientTexts.value: You can challenge up to 10 players in 1vs1 PVP duel and win Honor Points. The Duel ranking resets every week, rank high to receive special rewards!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_013
clientTexts.value: You can enter the Tomb of Ankou three times a day, team up with other players to fight the hordes of Masquerpets and defeat the boss!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_014
clientTexts.value: You can upgrade your gear up to +15 to reinforce its stats, but be careful, the upgrade may fail and you may lose upgrade levels if you didn't use a Scroll of Protection.

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_015
clientTexts.value: Monster Lair is full of EXP and items! Note that Monster Lair is only opened for a limited time per day!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_016
clientTexts.value: You may collect Orbs when you defeat Masquerpets. Add them to your Bestiary to increase your stats, and complete each continent collection for an extra buff!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_017
clientTexts.value: You can earn extra Penyas and EXP from La Christiana three times a day. Team up with other players and destroy La Christiana's engine!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_018
clientTexts.value: The Rested Bonus will give you extra EXP when you are afk for 1 minute or offline! You can accumulate the bonus EXP for up to 12h, and you may use Penya or Diamonds to increase the reward.

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_019
clientTexts.value: Party up with other players to share EXP, Mastery buffs and speed up your progress. You will surely complete the quests faster in a party than solo.

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_020
clientTexts.value: The Masquerpets are stealing my collection of books! Stop them from running away with my books and I will reward you for your efforts. Don't worry, the Masquerpets are distracted by my collection, so they won't attack you... but there's quite a number of

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_021
clientTexts.value: Complete the Hunt Quests every day to earn Soulbound Diamonds. Finish all the Hunt Quests and you will receive additional Soulbound Diamonds!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_022
clientTexts.value: Check your achievements to track your progress. You will receive Soulbound Diamonds as well as Glory Points that will give you new Titles and buffs!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_023
clientTexts.value: You can challenge strong bosses in the Colosseum twice a day, but remember that if you exit before the battle is over, you won't be able to claim the rewards.

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_024
clientTexts.value: You can earn Penya, Oricalkums, and other items from the Endless Tower. The higher you go, the stronger the Masquerpets and the better the rewards!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_025
clientTexts.value: You can dismantle unused gear to receive Magic Powders. High rarity gear will yield a more Magic Powders, but you may want to keep some gear for the Fusion as well...

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_026
clientTexts.value: Runes are special items that can be found in certain dungeons. You can socket Runes onto your gear to gain additional stats, choose wisely what is best for your character!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_027
clientTexts.value: Gems are special materials that are required to Ultimate Upgrade your gear. Be cautious with what gem you use for your gear, choose wisely!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_028
clientTexts.value: You can exchange Penya, Diamonds, or Magic Powder for any items in the Exchange Store. The stocks are limited each day, but you will increase with your VIP level.

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_029
clientTexts.value: You can check other's ranking! Check who's the strongest, the richest, and victory records!

clientTexts.name: A29_TXT_030
clientTexts.value: Test your skills in the PvP Arena and receive EXP and Honor Points! The Arena is only opened at a certain time each day, and the winner will receive special rewards and powerful buff!

clientTexts.name: CHAPTER_DESC_0001
clientTexts.value: Once upon a time, in the quiet and peaceful town of Flarine... There was a sudden explosion in occurrences of Masquerpet invasions. And while that wasn't a good thing, it allowed me to join a band of Masquerpet hunters. After defeating the great scorpion

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0002
clientTexts.value: I brewed that special potion the mayor gave you myself, so tell me how it works after you try it! ...Uh, not that I don't know what it does! I've totally tested it before! Ha ha ha...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0003
clientTexts.value: You here to sign up as a Soldier of Kyon? Okay, greenhorn, first get out there and kill some Aibatts. They're a right menace for the whole town.

clientTexts.name: CHAPTER_DESC_0002
clientTexts.value: Famous after defeating Chaner, I was able to retrieve the cryptic prophecy scroll. After finding the scroll, I faced an enigmatic Violet Magician. The magician treated me like an old friend, but I don't remember ever meeting him before...

clientTexts.name: CHAPTER_DESC_0003
clientTexts.value: Before he died, the Violet Magician mentioned something about missing children... Intrigued by his words, I started chasing clues—straight into a battle with a giant Red Mantis. By the time I defeated it, the children were already gone. Who kidnapped thos

clientTexts.name: CHAPTER_DESC_0004
clientTexts.value: After finding out that Ivillis Quaker kidnapped the children to use in a resurrection ritual of Yoon, I headed towards the Ivillis Temple. Even though Ivillis Quaker was defeated, Yoon was resurrected. Unfortunately, some children had been sacrificed.

clientTexts.name: CHAPTER_DESC_0005
clientTexts.value: Yoon's actions led to the disappearance of even more children. Luckily, during the search, I was able to catch up with Yoon and the Demon King Astaroth. I seriously injured Yoon, but the missing children were whisked away by Masquerpets.

clientTexts.name: CHAPTER_DESC_0006
clientTexts.value: By now, the parents of the kidnapped children were incredibly distraught, so I put together a rescue operation as soon as I could. And it worked—I was able to rescue the kids even more easily than I'd expected. A hunch tells me there's something fishy abo

clientTexts.name: CHAPTER_DESC_0007
clientTexts.value: Turns out that the Demon King Astaroth is gathering rare Dekane Ore to absorb children's souls. I took out the Kikun Tribe, who'd been gathering materials for Astaroth. However, they were able to deliver some ore to the demon.

clientTexts.name: CHAPTER_DESC_0008
clientTexts.value: By using Masquerpets as a decoy, I was able to find Astaroth's location. The mercenaries were able to defeat Astaroth before he could absorb the children's souls, and got the kids back home.

clientTexts.name: CHAPTER_DESC_0009
clientTexts.value: After a tough battle, I defeated the Demon King Astaroth. But his followers still remain. They've been hiding out in the recently discovered territory of Shaduwar. With the help of many, I reached Shaduwar. Now, with the help of the locals, I depart to lo

clientTexts.name: CHAPTER_DESC_0010
clientTexts.value: While almost all the missing children were found, Vespu, leader of the expedition party, got injured during the search. Searching for an apothecary, I entered the Eastia Canyon in the north. There, I faced a surprising truth that no one had ever known...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0001
clientTexts.value: Hey, adventurer! Since you've been so busy with the recent outbreak of Masquerpets, the mayor's prepared some special gifts for you to keep your spirits up! Oh, and Luda at the market is looking for you, too.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0004
clientTexts.value: Got rid of those Aibatts, did you? Nice work. They've been keeping me from gathering materials.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0005
clientTexts.value: So you're the newest member of the Kyon Soldiers... The peace of Flaris is in your hands. We're counting on you.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0006
clientTexts.value: Although mercenaries are fighting the Masquerpets, there are just too many of them... Your help would really be appreciated.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0007
clientTexts.value: Never seen a warrior with a pet before? You can get yourself a rabbit from the hill if you want. Best of all, it's free!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0008
clientTexts.value: I've seen lots of mercenaries, but you've got skills and a great attitude!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0009
clientTexts.value: Did you hear the news? Masquerpets are causing troubles at Madren Town.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0010
clientTexts.value: To beat Masquerpets, mercenaries should fight together. Can we count on your help from now on?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0011
clientTexts.value: You will need powerful weapons to fight against Masquerpets. How about looking for one at Madren Town?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0012
clientTexts.value: Head down to Madren Town first. It's a long way from here, but you won't be so lonely with a rabbit.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0013
clientTexts.value: I heard that you took care of a bunch of Masquerpets near Flaris. Nice, but don't get a swelled head over it!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0014
clientTexts.value: Once the Brudengs were taken out, Captain Brudeng's gone out of control! Take care of it, would you?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0015
clientTexts.value: Go and meet up with Tucani near Madren Town. He might know something. Be aware of Pukepuke on the road there.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0016
clientTexts.value: Rumor has it that a giant scorpion named Chaner appeared around Madren Town. Usually Masquerpets don't fight each other, but it seems like the Demians were pushed out of their habitat because of that scorpion.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0017
clientTexts.value: I've seen that Chaner, and it's terrifying! You can't let it destroy the town, you've got to kill it, please!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0018
clientTexts.value: Chaner attacks with the huge stinger on its tail. Be careful... Still, I think you're the one that can defeat Chaner, and make the Demians to go back to their homes.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0019
clientTexts.value: Go defeat Chaner! It will be a great opportunity to get good items.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0020
clientTexts.value: Welcome, I heard a lot about you from Mikyel. We could also use your help here in the Leren Mountains...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0021
clientTexts.value: I've heard rumors about strange things happening in the Leren Mountains, but now that there's so many mercenaries, it's gotta be true.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0022
clientTexts.value: I don't know why, but Masquerpets are going out of control. We need to do something about it.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0023
clientTexts.value: Things are only getting worse. We'll need more strength to handle the troubles coming our way. Find companions to help you!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0024
clientTexts.value: You've got a good look to you... Yeah, I feel confident you can save the Leren Mountains! By the way, Pupit is looking for you.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0025
clientTexts.value: Something's going on at the Plain of Bubble. Please find Captain Teshar.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0026
clientTexts.value: Are you looking for Captain Teshar? I might be able to help....if you can take out Fefern for me. I can't get materials because of that thing.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0027
clientTexts.value: Thank you. Captain Teshar is probably somewhere around the Tomb of Ankou.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0028
clientTexts.value: Huh, the Tomb of Ankou? Go straight and follow this road. You'll pass a bunch of Bangs, so feel free to take some of them out.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0029
clientTexts.value: Thank you so much. It will be easier to defend because of you. Captain Teshar is with Radion.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0030
clientTexts.value: Looking for Teshar? You must be the one who just joined the mercenaries. Follow this road, you won't be able to miss her.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0031
clientTexts.value: Impressive… I accept you as a formal member of our mercenary band. Go find Gran, let's celebrate!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0032
clientTexts.value: I can't believe Teshar invited you to the Tomb of Ankou, how interesting... The Tomb of Ankou is actually located in the sky. You'll need this magic broom.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0033
clientTexts.value: Back already!? Don't tell me it was too easy for you... Seriously, unbelievable...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0034
clientTexts.value: You can obtain a huge amount of EXP and items from the Masquerpets inside the Tomb of Ankou. Tempting, huh?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0035
clientTexts.value: A group of bandits called Bang stole the ancient prophecy scroll. What can I do? Can you help me?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0036
clientTexts.value: You brought the prophecy scroll! Thank you...it's very meaningful to me. Have you heard of the  creatures called Ivillis? ...Forget about this book for now. Let's focus on what's happening at the Plain of Bubble.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0037
clientTexts.value: The forces gathering on Plain Of Bubble... I found out they came from the Violet Magician. Please stop him!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0038
clientTexts.value: Seems like there is connection between the missing children and Masquerpets. I'll investigate more.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0039
clientTexts.value: Could you do me a favor?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0040
clientTexts.value: Thanks for delivering the letter. I'll look into the missing kids, too.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0041
clientTexts.value: Upgrading your equipment improves their basic stats so you can handle Masquerpets more easily than before.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0042
clientTexts.value: Hey, don't forget to upgrade from time to time. Right, I have to teach the rookies how to upgrade!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0043
clientTexts.value: I heard you killed Prankster? Remember, Prankster is a low-class captain. You will face much stronger Masquerpets, so be careful.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0044
clientTexts.value: You'll need strong equipment to face down strong Masquerpets. You can combine equipment to transform it to higher tiers, so you'll always wanna be collecting new gear!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0045
clientTexts.value: Please keep up your training to fight Masquerpets. Checking mandatory quests is a efficient way to train.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0046
clientTexts.value: Orphans are missing! Children with families have started going missing, too!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0047
clientTexts.value: We've created a guild to protect our children...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0048
clientTexts.value: But children who aren't under the guild's protection are still missing. We need to look for clues!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0049
clientTexts.value: I'm worried about the missing children. Heard they were kidnapped by Masquerpets... I hope they're okay.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0050
clientTexts.value: We are searching Masquerpet lairs to find the missing children. Hopefully we'll find them as soon as possible.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0051
clientTexts.value: Huh... I wonder how the Masquerpets could get in and kidnap anyone...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0052
clientTexts.value: We still haven't found any clues, but the Mia in this area might know something.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0053
clientTexts.value: The Masquerpets around here haven't left us any clues... You're gonna need to go farther out. Try checking out the Auction House for your preparations.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0054
clientTexts.value: I hope we can rescue the kids unharmed.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0055
clientTexts.value: Funny how everyone who just sat quiet when the orphans disappeared started pushing for rescue parties once their own children started going missing.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0056
clientTexts.value: Finding the Mia is important, but don't forget you'll have to fight them after you find them!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0057
clientTexts.value: Do you know about La Christiana? There are many Masquerpets there. I wish I knew more about it...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0058
clientTexts.value: It's definitely strange that there are so many Masquerpets in La Christiana.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0059
clientTexts.value: Yep. That's why I sent someone to check La Christiana out.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0060
clientTexts.value: Ah, and they're back. Hold on a moment.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0061
clientTexts.value: Unfortunately... According to the person I sent to investigate, there's no one in La Christiana but Masquerpets.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0062
clientTexts.value: Ugh... At this rate, it'd be faster to just start sending out search parties for the children.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0063
clientTexts.value: Apparently there is a witness who saw the children. Please talk ask Pierce for more information.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0064
clientTexts.value: Thanks for getting rid of that Mr. Pumpkin. Yes, I saw the children with my own eyes!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0065
clientTexts.value: I have a bad feeling about this. Please stop the Masquerpets before it's too late.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0066
clientTexts.value: Looks like this is the start of a full-blown adventure! Don't neglect your equipment, okay? Your life literally depends on it.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0067
clientTexts.value: There is a new frightening Masquerpet called the Red Mantis. Do you think you can handle it?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0068
clientTexts.value: Beware of the Red Mantis' razor-sharp arms, even the corpses of its victims are hardly recognizable...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0069
clientTexts.value: I think the Red Mantis is the key to find the missing children. We need to defeat it no matter what it takes.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0070
clientTexts.value: Please ask Nomierr, he is the one who saw the Red Mantis.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0071
clientTexts.value: We need to hurry before they use the children for the ritual. Prepare your gear and let's go!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0072
clientTexts.value: Bobochan makes great equipment. Go talk to him.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0073
clientTexts.value: Here's my latest creation, made from only the finest materials! You'd like to have it, wouldn't you. I suppose I can trade it...if you have enough Magic Powders.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0074
clientTexts.value: Looks like they've made their move. Let's hurry.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0075
clientTexts.value: We got a few leads, but we still don't know who they are resurrecting.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0076
clientTexts.value: Masquerpets have invaded the Hillid Mountains. Have you ever been there? It is much more dangerous than any place you've visited so far.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0077
clientTexts.value: In order to go there, you need to become more powerful. Please meet the Mysterious Girl and ask her about Rebirth.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0078
clientTexts.value: A Red Mantis has appeared on the way to Hillid Mountain. Please be careful.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0080
clientTexts.value: Finally, you made it. From what we gather, the children may have been taken to Ivillis Temple.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0081
clientTexts.value: I sense death... Maybe they've sacrificed the children already.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0079
clientTexts.value: Great work! Now you should go to Hillid Mountain. Elite troops have been sent there to investigate rumors of children disappearance. But it seems they ran into trouble... Can you check it out?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0082
clientTexts.value: Could you look for Nomierr? I heard he helped the Masquerpets.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0083
clientTexts.value: According to his sister Leminerr, Nomierr went to the Hillid Mountains after helping the Masquerpets.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0084
clientTexts.value: You will see people hunting Hobos near the mouth of the Hillid Mountains. Help them out and ask for Nomierr.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0085
clientTexts.value: Phew, that was close... Thanks for helping us.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0086
clientTexts.value: The Hillid Mountains are a very dangerous area. Not only are they crawling with Masquerpets, but the mountains themselves are dangerous. But if you're dead-set on going, I won't stop you.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0087
clientTexts.value: Did I see Nomierr? Oh yeah, there's no way I would forget someone with such a bizarre giggle.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0088
clientTexts.value: There are many rumors about the Hillid Mountains. That's one of the reasons so many people come here, despite the danger.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0089
clientTexts.value: The biggest rumor is that there are some very valuable ores in the Hillid Mountains. However, while a ton of people have gone looking for them, I've never seen anyone come back... Not alive, anyway.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0090
clientTexts.value: Don't go there looking for ore or materials. Your life is more important than some stuff.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0091
clientTexts.value: I'm the only one who survived. Everyone else was killed by Dumb Bulls.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0092
clientTexts.value: I'm finally able to escape this hellish place, thanks to you. I'll never be able to repay you.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0093
clientTexts.value: Unbelievable! There is a survivor! This is all thanks to your efforts.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0094
clientTexts.value: Wow, you fought Masquerpets in the Hillid Mountains with this old equipment? Definitely try the Upgrade option. Fighting Masquerpets will be much easier!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0095
clientTexts.value: I know there are people south of the Hillid mountains. Go ask them about Nomierr.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0096
clientTexts.value: Did you see my brother Nomierr? I can't believe he helped Masquerpets kidnap children...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0097
clientTexts.value: There must be some good reason he'd help Masquerpets do something so terrible. Please, help my brother!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0098
clientTexts.value: So, you finally made it... I was getting tired of waiting.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0099
clientTexts.value: Take it easy. I'm not here to fight.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0100
clientTexts.value: Urghhh...my head... Where is this? Leminerr... Where's my team...where's my sister!?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0101
clientTexts.value: The Masquerpets are getting stronger. We need to get stronger--and quick.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0102
clientTexts.value: You should do the daily quests from Mikyel. It is the fast way to get stronger and gain some extra Stardust!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0103
clientTexts.value: Handel, Parine, and Helena went to Ivillis Leanes Temple. They should be able to take care of themselves...but look after them just in case.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0104
clientTexts.value: Hello, I've heard quite a bit about you. We found that the Ivillis Quaker has taken over Ivillis Leanes Temple.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0105
clientTexts.value: Masquerpets are gathering at Ivillis Leanes Temple. They are definitely up to something.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0106
clientTexts.value: Don't forget to save the children. Defeating Ivillis Quaker might put the children in danger. So let's be careful.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0107
clientTexts.value: We'll have to fight smart. Let's start by reducing the number of Masquerpets around, first.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0108
clientTexts.value: First, let's find Parine. While we cull some Masquerpets with her, I'll work out how to take out Ivillis Quaker.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0109
clientTexts.value: So boring... These guys're so weak it's a real snoozefest! How about you go toe-to-toe with me?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0110
clientTexts.value: My master is too serious. All we have to do is kill the Ivillis Quaker and save the kids. Easy peasy, don't you think?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0111
clientTexts.value: I'm going to go to the Ivillis Leanes Temple, so I need you to handle these Ivillis Guardians. You can do that, right?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0112
clientTexts.value: Oh, impressive. Nicely done. Talk to my master.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0113
clientTexts.value: Well done. However, it is too quiet inside of the temple... Please go check if Handel knows anything.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0114
clientTexts.value: Seems like they started a summoning ritual. I can feel powerful forces.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0115
clientTexts.value: We'd better stay away from here. Tell Pupit about this, okay?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0116
clientTexts.value: If we don't deal with this now, it will get much worse later on.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0117
clientTexts.value: Our only chance to slay the Ivillis Quaker is now before the summoning ritual is complete.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0118
clientTexts.value: That's what Pupit said? ...Alright. What does Helena think?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0119
clientTexts.value: I agree with Pupit. Now is the only chance before the summoning is completed.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0120
clientTexts.value: We can't all go. Some of us need to stay and deal with the Masquerpets before they overrun the place.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0121
clientTexts.value: Well done fighting with Ivillis Quaker. Did you find the children yet?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0122
clientTexts.value: We couldn't stop Yoon's resurrection. He's so powerful... It's going to be tough to defeat him.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0123
clientTexts.value: Welcome back, though I wish it was under happier circumstances. It's a real pity so many children were sacrificed.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0124
clientTexts.value: We've tracked Yoon to the Rhisis' Garden. No idea why Ivillis Quaker summoned him, though.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0125
clientTexts.value: Please rest up and when you're ready, talk to the mercenary. He will tell you how to get to the Rhisis' Garden.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0126
clientTexts.value: Finally ready to go to the Rhisis' Garden, huh? It's a dangerous place, so stay on your guard.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0127
clientTexts.value: After Yoon appeared in the Rhisis' Garden, more children went missing.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0128
clientTexts.value: I heard a rumor that Yoon played some strange tune, and people just lost their minds. Once they recovered, their children were missing.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0129
clientTexts.value: There must be some kind of power in Yoon's musical performance.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0130
clientTexts.value: There must be something that only affects kids when Masquerpets are sealed in Collections.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0131
clientTexts.value: Enough standing around! We need to investigate this ability of Yoon's as soon as possible!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0132
clientTexts.value: We're too weak to get much done like this. But to improve, we'll need funds.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0133
clientTexts.value: Head to Saint Dock and hunt Masquerpets there. That should be a solid way to make some money.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0134
clientTexts.value: I've finally figured out where Yoon is. I really want to take him out now, but I don't want put the children in danger. Let's gather more information.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0135
clientTexts.value: Yoon is heading to the Colosseum to save his chancellors who are imprisoned there.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0136
clientTexts.value: Yoon would be even more difficult to defeat with his chancellors. Let's kill the chancellors before it's too late!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0137
clientTexts.value: They are imprisoned here, but still very powerful. It's not going to be easy. I wish you the best of luck.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0138
clientTexts.value: We are gathering information on Yoon's abilities. I'm sure we will have a solution soon.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0139
clientTexts.value: I know of a training place that helps you boost combat experience quickly.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0140
clientTexts.value: It's a small place, so you might want to avoid the busiest times, but do keep up your training.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0141
clientTexts.value: How's the practice going? Karandur is looking for you.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0142
clientTexts.value: Finally, we have information about Yoon's ability. Both adults and children can hear that sound.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0143
clientTexts.value: For adults, it just makes them mindless, but children are lured by it.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0144
clientTexts.value: If we could find a way to modulate that sound into a different one, we would be able to fight off Yoon.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0145
clientTexts.value: Many heroes use the Arena to test their abilities. The last man standing gets a special blessing. Let's hurry over there!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0146
clientTexts.value: A group of parents who learned of Yoon's location have struck up a rescue plan of their own.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0147
clientTexts.value: I sympathize, I really do, but we need to stop them.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0148
clientTexts.value: A poorly-thought-out rescue plan could put the children in more danger. First of all, let's buy some time by pretending to help them.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0149
clientTexts.value: We've figured out why Yoon is working with Astaroth. After Astaroth absorbs the children, Yoon plans to attack Astaroth and absorb all the power for himself.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0150
clientTexts.value: We need to get rid of the Masquerpets while they're distracted.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0151
clientTexts.value: How you been? It's very nice to see you again.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0152
clientTexts.value: How about killing our common foe? It'd be mutually beneficial, wouldn't it? You don't have anything to lose.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0153
clientTexts.value: If you agreed, I would've told you how to easily defeat him, but too bad.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0154
clientTexts.value: Ha ha... See you next time, rookie.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0155
clientTexts.value: Ugh, what a headache! Let's help Hamel slay the Masquerpets first. Then we'll chase after Yoon.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0156
clientTexts.value: Strange… The number of Masquerpets is staying steady.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0157
clientTexts.value: Yoon must've done something. The Masquerpet population is growing fast!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0158
clientTexts.value: Tch... The people I've got tracking Yoon contacted us, but it's not good news. A ton of Masquerpets have suddenly appeared and are gathering around Yoon.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0159
clientTexts.value: Time is short, so I'll help you with weapon synthesis. Take this weapon. I'll give you some Magic Powder, too.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0160
clientTexts.value: Yoon's been fighting the Masquerpets. Seems like he's not the one causing the outbreak.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0161
clientTexts.value: Astaroth already knew Yoon's plan. Astaroth sent all those Masquerpets to stop him.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0162
clientTexts.value: Yoon is trying to become the Demon King instead of Astaroth. We can't let it happen.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0163
clientTexts.value: To defeat Yoon, you need more powerful skills. Let me open the Party Dungeon so you can improve yourself.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0164
clientTexts.value: Anyway, the conflict between Yoon and Astaroth gives us a great opportunity. I want to keep a close eye on the situation.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0165
clientTexts.value: Them working against each other is certainly a good thing, but they are unlikely to want to fight face-to-face.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0166
clientTexts.value: In a direct battle, no matter which of them won, both would suffer heavy losses. However, if they were to agree to help each other instead, it would be our worst-case scenario.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0167
clientTexts.value: Hm... Seems like it'd be best for us to take out Yoon as quickly as possible.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0168
clientTexts.value: Hm... Astaroth is out of control. This is big trouble.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0169
clientTexts.value: Astaroth is trying to absorb not only the children, but also Yoon's soul!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0170
clientTexts.value: If we don't keep Astaroth from doing that, we're going to have a time of it.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0171
clientTexts.value: As I expected, Astaroth is one step ahead of Yoon.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0172
clientTexts.value: Astaroth is sending Masquerpets to kidnap children, but also wasting Yoon's power.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0173
clientTexts.value: Maybe Astaroth's plan is to absorb Yoon's power while he's weak. We need to get Yoon before Astaroth can.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0174
clientTexts.value: Yoon was injured by Masquerpets, and is hiding out in the Dwarpet Ruins. Now is the chance to take them all out.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0175
clientTexts.value: Well done. We stopped kept Astaroth from absorbing Yoon's power.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0176
clientTexts.value: Now it's time to rescue the children before it's too late!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0177
clientTexts.value: It'll take Astaroth time to absorb all the children's souls. Before that happens, let's move!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0178
clientTexts.value: Oh no... The rain washed away Yoon's tracks. How do we find the children now?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0179
clientTexts.value: Recently, the parents who've lost their children have been making even more of a fuss.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0180
clientTexts.value: I think that they heard about the sacrifices for Yoon's ressurection...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0181
clientTexts.value: That was supposed to be kept secret! How in the world did they find out?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0182
clientTexts.value: I heard you've been looking for the kids...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0183
clientTexts.value: I saw them! Well...kind of. They were all fuzzy due to fog.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0184
clientTexts.value: But it was such an unusual thing that I remember it clear as day. The other members of the expedition team saw it, too.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0185
clientTexts.value: This is the way to the Rhisis' Garden. We were able to chase them this far.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0186
clientTexts.value: I'd like to keep chatting, but I need to go to Cloud Crater. It's a mysterious place that has various rare materials.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0187
clientTexts.value: Please ask one of our members for more information.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0188
clientTexts.value: Oh yeah, I saw the shadow of the kids just like the chief did. Seemed like they were possessed by something...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0189
clientTexts.value: They were moving too fast though, we couldn't catch up. So we've been following their trail since then.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0190
clientTexts.value: The parents knew all about what happened to the kids.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0191
clientTexts.value: They knew not only about the sacrifices for Yoon's resurrection, but also about how Nomierr helped the Masquerpets.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0192
clientTexts.value: And they're furious about it, understandably. They want more information about the kids and Nomierr.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0193
clientTexts.value: They've put out rewards to hunt down Masquerpets, but I'm pretty sure it won't be long before we're their next target.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0194
clientTexts.value: I'm pretty sure that somebody is leaking the information on purpose.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0195
clientTexts.value: I think maybe some Masquerpets did it... They have nothing to lose from it.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0196
clientTexts.value: And excluding us and Yoon, they are the only ones who know what's going on.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0197
clientTexts.value: Yeah... Maybe Astaroth is trying to get us to fight within ourselves so we'll be weaker.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0198
clientTexts.value: Indeed. I'm sure it is possible if it's Astaroth.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0199
clientTexts.value: We need to stop this before it's too late. We definitely need another plan.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0200
clientTexts.value: Apparently the missing children have turned up. Would you like to meet Raundas?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0201
clientTexts.value: I found a witness who saw the children.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0202
clientTexts.value: The Masquerpet with the children is huge, and carries a big hammer.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0203
clientTexts.value: Sounds like Jaken... He's slow, but very powerful.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0204
clientTexts.value: I'm sure we could find him easily if he is Jaken.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0205
clientTexts.value: Yes! He is Jaken, but something's wrong.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0206
clientTexts.value: To be fair, I was pretty far from them. Even so, I'm pretty sure that wasn't enough. Some of the children were missing.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0207
clientTexts.value: Is that true? We are still missing children?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0208
clientTexts.value: If that was true, where are the other kids?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0209
clientTexts.value: We can't stop their parents if the same thing happens again.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0210
clientTexts.value: Most importantly, let's make sure this information stays between us. In the meantime, please make sure this doesn't happen again.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0211
clientTexts.value: Sorry about all this. We'd like to stay with you, but the rest of the crew needs to resolve the chaos in the village.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0212
clientTexts.value: Maybe this is our chance to make things right. If it works out, they should trust us again!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0213
clientTexts.value: Yes, I heard many children were missing.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0214
clientTexts.value: We can't look for them right now because we're busy dealing with the people who are furious about Masquerpets.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0215
clientTexts.value: Therefore, I'm the only one left to work on this, but honestly this is not easy at all.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0216
clientTexts.value: We need to focus on this situation. If we don't, it is going to be worse than before.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0217
clientTexts.value: To calm the furious parents, we told them we could rescue children for sure, but we actually aren't that sure at all.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0218
clientTexts.value: If this plan fails, we are in serious trouble.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0219
clientTexts.value: Not only do we lose the people's trust, but they'll head off to fight Masquerpets without proper preparation.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0220
clientTexts.value: In that case, the Masquerpets will succeed in their plans.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0221
clientTexts.value: Astaroth would regain his power, and we would collapse without a single blow.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0222
clientTexts.value: Just as we wanted infighting between Yoon and Astaroth, Astaroth wants us to fight, too.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0223
clientTexts.value: Once he fully recovers, Astaroth himself will come to finish us off.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0224
clientTexts.value: I don't know why, but the shadows of the kids only appear where it's easy to see them.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0225
clientTexts.value: Perhaps they are luring us in, just like fishing.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0226
clientTexts.value: The kids are being thrown out as bait for us... It's daring, but I don't know how else to think about it.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0227
clientTexts.value: Even if it's a trap, we have to go for it.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0228
clientTexts.value: We told the parents that we'd act, and if we don't succeed, they'll take matters into their own hands.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0230
clientTexts.value: I'm sorry. We can't help you this time. Head on to the Endless Tower.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0231
clientTexts.value: I apologize that we can't support you. We wish you the best of luck. Please come back safe.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0232
clientTexts.value: Finally, you were able to rescue the children! ...Though it seems like there are still some missing.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0233
clientTexts.value: That said, rescuing some of them is still better than none of them!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0234
clientTexts.value: We were able to recover the trust of some parents, and hopefully we can earn the trust of the rest. And we'll do something to compensate the parents whose children were sacrificed...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0235
clientTexts.value: Thanks for your help with such an important task. Unfortunately, we couldn't rescue all the kids.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0236
clientTexts.value: As far as I can tell, it seems like they leaked their location on purpose.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0237
clientTexts.value: I don't know what's up with the other kids. But some Masquerpets were spotted heading to the Dekane Mine in Darkon.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0238
clientTexts.value: Are you ready to head to Darkon? Darkon has a lot of dangerous Masquerpets.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0239
clientTexts.value: Since we don't have a way to track the children, we should try to get some information out of the Masquerpets.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0240
clientTexts.value: Yes, I think that's the best plan. Hope the Masquerpets know something.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0241
clientTexts.value: Let's gather some information about Dekane Mine, first.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0242
clientTexts.value: It's like a tomb for mechanical Masquerpets.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0243
clientTexts.value: Mechanical Masquerpets are made out of machines that people threw out.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0244
clientTexts.value: So most mechanical Masquerpets are hostile towards humans because of those memories.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0245
clientTexts.value: Track down the Masquerpets we're looking for, and slay all the rest. It's a big task, but just take them one step at a time.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0246
clientTexts.value: Let's take out those Leyena and Trangfoma to buy some time.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0247
clientTexts.value: Good job. We still don't know much about the Dekane Mine, though.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0248
clientTexts.value: We have new information. Masquerpets are gathering materials for a machine to help Astaroth absorb souls.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0249
clientTexts.value: I'm not sure what materials they need, however.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0250
clientTexts.value: If we tail them, we can learn what they're looking for.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0251
clientTexts.value: Are you heading to the Dekane Mine?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0252
clientTexts.value: I have an ancient slate, but reading it is slow going... It's all written in some ancient language, you see.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0253
clientTexts.value: So far, I know these slates are about the Dekane Mine.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0254
clientTexts.value: I can translate them, but it will take some time.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0255
clientTexts.value: I made rubbings of the slates... Please deliver them to Mirian.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0256
clientTexts.value: She is the expert at understanding ancient languages.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0257
clientTexts.value: I think the content of the slates will be a big help in getting through the mines.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0258
clientTexts.value: I appreciate your help. Give my best to Mirian, would you?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0259
clientTexts.value: Oh! Esope sent you? Please wait a minute.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0260
clientTexts.value: This is written in the language of the ancients... It's about Dekane Mine.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0261
clientTexts.value: There are unique minerals in the mines. This slate is talking about them.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0263
clientTexts.value: Wow, I can't believe there are unique minerals in the Dekane Mine.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0264
clientTexts.value: I'm pretty sure the Masquerpets are after those minerals.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0265
clientTexts.value: They want to use them to build a machine to help Astaroth.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0266
clientTexts.value: Let's hurry. More children are in danger if the Masquerpets get their hands on those minerals.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0267
clientTexts.value: Not only must we stop the Masquerpets from gathering the minerals, but also we need to recover the minerals the Masquerpets already have.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0268
clientTexts.value: We don't know how much they need to build the machine, so we'd better stop them quick.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0269
clientTexts.value: Oh... I knew Masquerpets were up to something in the mines!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0270
clientTexts.value: I'm pretty sure the Kikun Tribe will go into Dekane Mine. We'd better hurry.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0271
clientTexts.value: The minerals must be buried really deep in the mines. That's why no one knows about them.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0272
clientTexts.value: We need more information about the inside of Dekane Mine.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0273
clientTexts.value: If there's only one entrance and exit, it will be easy to meet up. If not, we could get split up for a while.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0275
clientTexts.value: The Kikun Tribe just started gathering the materials. Now is the time.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0276
clientTexts.value: Some people were gathering materials, too. I don't know how they knew about them...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0277
clientTexts.value: Since the Kikun Tribe didn't notice us, this is our chance to stop them.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0278
clientTexts.value: Well done! We stopped the Kikun Tribe from gathering the minerals.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0279
clientTexts.value: Hm... We stopped the Kikun Tribe, and it was pretty simple...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0280
clientTexts.value: I don't like it. They could have something else up their sleeves.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0281
clientTexts.value: I agree. They gave up so quickly...too quickly.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0282
clientTexts.value: Maybe they were hypnotized by Yoon, too.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0283
clientTexts.value: Maybe... Well, we find them, we'll find the truth. If that is the case, it's not going to be good.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0284
clientTexts.value: I saw people gathering things in the Dekane Mine.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0285
clientTexts.value: They took the materials and headed to Rustia.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0286
clientTexts.value: Seriously? There must be a reason they retreated to Rustia.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0287
clientTexts.value: Yeah... The reason the Kikun Tribe gave up so easily was because they'd already finished gathering their materials. We have to go after them.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0288
clientTexts.value: The most powerful of them must be the Beast King Khan. Let's hurry after them!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0289
clientTexts.value: Even though Beast King Khan was defeated, the materials have already been transported elsewhere. It's terrible... I appreciate your efforts, at least.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0290
clientTexts.value: They left Masquerpets in Rustia to buy themselves time.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0291
clientTexts.value: But we've sent some members after the Masquerpets, so we're praying for good results.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0292
clientTexts.value: We don't have much time since they took the materials. We better hurry.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0293
clientTexts.value: All members have been mobilized. We'll meet up with everyone else further on.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0294
clientTexts.value: Welcome! Fortunately, the Masquerpets haven't noticed us yet.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0295
clientTexts.value: Astaroth is hidden in this rugged terrain... It makes a natural shield.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0296
clientTexts.value: Were we to fight here, we could suffer some serious damage.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0297
clientTexts.value: The Masquerpets are so slow, they must be getting farther and farther away from the people carrying the minerals.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0298
clientTexts.value: There's no point in chasing after the Masquerpets if we can't keep the minerals from being delivered to Astaroth.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0299
clientTexts.value: We need to do something to make them move faster than before.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0300
clientTexts.value: Astaroth has both strength and wisdom. I heard Astaroth's strength comes from the souls of the living.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0301
clientTexts.value: The younger the soul, the easier it is to extract its energy.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0302
clientTexts.value: We have to hurry. With that equipment, absorbing the souls from the kids will be child's play. ...No pun intended.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0303
clientTexts.value: Something is not quite right here.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0304
clientTexts.value: Ack! Grrr noticed our scent and started tracking us!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0305
clientTexts.value: We need to take out the Masquerpets before they notice us.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0306
clientTexts.value: Not bad... We were quick, but some of them noticed something was up.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0307
clientTexts.value: Look, their movement's changed. I hope they didn't see us...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0308
clientTexts.value: Fortunately, they haven't noticed us yet, though they're even more on their guard.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0309
clientTexts.value: Thank goodness, they're moving faster than before.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0310
clientTexts.value: If we don't lose them, we should be able to stop the minerals from being delivered!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0311
clientTexts.value: Be careful, don't let them see you! If they spot us, the jig is up!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0312
clientTexts.value: I dunno... I think they don't have enough materials to make the soul-sucking machine work perfectly.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0313
clientTexts.value: I see... If Bernard says it, it must be true.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0314
clientTexts.value: Good to know. So the machine's output shouldn't be as efficient as the Masquerpets are planning on.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0315
clientTexts.value: That'll be good information for when we face Astaroth.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0316
clientTexts.value: The Masquerpets are moving slower than before, and tightened their guard.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0317
clientTexts.value: They are preparing to teleport to their stronghold.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0318
clientTexts.value: We need to watch them closely to see how they teleport to their stronghold.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0319
clientTexts.value: I'm pretty sure we can't use that method.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0320
clientTexts.value: However, I just received the grimoire on teleportation, so we will figure it out soon.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0321
clientTexts.value: Hm... Bernard is having a hard time figuring it out.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0322
clientTexts.value: Sorry. It's all written in the language of the ancients, so translation took a long time.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0323
clientTexts.value: I've figured out the coordinates... I don't know where it leads, but I can teleport you there!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0325
clientTexts.value: Hello. I'm Radyan. I'm the one of the hostages. I'm hiding from Minimusha.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0326
clientTexts.value: Run away! The powerful Masquerpet Minimusha is around here!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0327
clientTexts.value: Before you guys showed up, people carrying some big bags came through. They must've been kidnapped, like me.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0328
clientTexts.value: They followed this road with Masquerpets.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0329
clientTexts.value: We better hurry before it's too late. Even though the Masquerpets don't have enough of the minerals, they can still build the machine.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0330
clientTexts.value: Of course, it won't be perfect since they're missing so many materials.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0331
clientTexts.value: It's going to take a lot to take down Astaroth... Let's make our preparations first, and then teleport to attack.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0332
clientTexts.value: It is going to be hard facing Astaroth.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0334
clientTexts.value: We will head out once everyone is ready. Gather here once you've done everything you need to do.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0335
clientTexts.value: We need to complete two missions... That's gonna be tough.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0336
clientTexts.value: Killing Astaroth and rescuing the kids won't be a walk in the park, either...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0337
clientTexts.value: Let's meet Bernard. He is waiting for us.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0338
clientTexts.value: Heading to Bernard? I'm ready too, so let's go together.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0339
clientTexts.value: Seems everyone is ready. Let's move deeper in than before.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0340
clientTexts.value: I'm gonna teleport you... Here goes.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0341
clientTexts.value: Thank goodness, we were able to save the children! The adults who were kidnapped can also come back home with their kids.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0342
clientTexts.value: We need to prepare so that there is no further damage. I'm going to investigate Astaroth's airship.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0343
clientTexts.value: Well done! I heard you defeated Astaroth.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0344
clientTexts.value: You don't look too happy... I heard the news, some of the children were absorbed. It's terrible, but there is nothing you can do about them now. Don't get too down about it...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0345
clientTexts.value: Bernard found out the coordinates the airship left from. Now we can find out where Astaroth's lair was.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0346
clientTexts.value: It's so far away, we'll need to take an airship to get there. I don't even know what the location is called.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0347
clientTexts.value: There are probably even more powerful Masquerpets at our destination. We can't just laze around...we've gotta prepare for some serious fighting.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0349
clientTexts.value: Welcome, how goes? Do you have something for me? Let me see... Okay, okay. This is Katna! I thought this mission would be difficult. Anyway, thank you so much.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0351
clientTexts.value: Huh, what is this? Looks like some kind of code... Sorry, but I think this is out of my expertise. Why don't you have a sage look at it? There's one in eastern Flaris.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0348
clientTexts.value: Warrior... Hey, you! Could you do me a favor? I need you to deliver this book to Mr. Luda for me. I've got an urgent meeting of the merchants' guild to attend, yanno? So, will you take care of this for me?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0350
clientTexts.value: This book is Harmonin's journal. My great-grandfather was a friend of his, and he always proudly told me he is a explorer who discovered the continent of Shaduwar. A whole new continent! Pretty amazing, huh?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0352
clientTexts.value: Hello, it's been a while! So, Luda sent you? Alright. Give me the book and I'll see what I can do.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0353
clientTexts.value: Thank you for your patience. Harmonin seems to have had quite a breadth of knowledge. He even knew this ancient tribal language.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0354
clientTexts.value: There is very precious information on location, climate and life on the new continent in this book. I will deliver a translated copy to Mr. Luda, don't worry. You should visit Mikyel in Saint Morning. She is looking for you.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0355
clientTexts.value: Hello, Warrior... I have something to tell you, but it is strictly confidential. It will be a very big problem if people in Flarine or anywhere else learns about it, so you mustn't tell a soul. Think you can do that?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0356
clientTexts.value: Alright. You promised...so I'll tell you. After the last operation to defeat Astaroth, I contacted my sources. Don't be surprised, but I think Astaroth's actual base is on the new continent.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0357
clientTexts.value: Hey, don't shoot the messenger, Warrior! Honestly, I don't know the details, but if you visit Amadolka in the Rhisis' Garden, they should be able to tell you all about it. Good luck!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0358
clientTexts.value: Thank you for coming. I cannot explain this to you in detail in this urgent moment, but know this for certain: the remnants of Astaroth remain across the new continent.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0359
clientTexts.value: Perhaps some of the children who remain missing may be found there, yet I cannot say with any certainty. If you visit Ainher in Darkon East, she will tell you everything you need to know about the continent of Shaduwar.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0360
clientTexts.value: It's been a while. How have you been? We don't have a ton of time, so I'll get to it. The air currents over Shaduwar are rough, so much so that only two ships have ever made it there...intact, anyway.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0361
clientTexts.value: So if you were thinking about just zipping in and out as normal, think again. There's nothing for it but to teleport. Lucky for you, Radyan in Darkon West knows teleportation magic. Go and show her this letter and this Offer Seed, okay?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0362
clientTexts.value: Heya, Warrior. Long time no see. Thank you very much for last time. Thanks to you, the kidnapped children made it home safely. So, I got the rough overview of what's going on. You got an Offer Seed from Ainher, right?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0363
clientTexts.value: Ooh, I never expected to get such a cute letter at this age... Now, let me see... Okay, it says to send you to Shaduwar as fast as possible.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0364
clientTexts.value: Offer Seeds can save magic spells. I think the location of Shaduwar Continent has already been saved in this Offer Seed. Let me send you to Shaduwar now. Please come back safely!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0365
clientTexts.value: Holy moly! Someone suddenly appeared in the air! D-don't tell me you're a...gh-gh-gh-ghost!? ...If you are a ghost...g-go away! Damn it!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0366
clientTexts.value: You teleported here? I heard Madrigal's magic is high level, but I didn't know it could move people that far a distance in an instant! Welcome, welcome.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0367
clientTexts.value: Man, I'd love to just shot the breeze with you, but there's some crazy stuff going on here, again... Actually, could I strongarm you into doing some work for me?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0391
clientTexts.value: I've heard the news. You've done an excellent job... Your life is like a light in the dark. —Oh, and you have the Lere Powder! Now I can finish the translation of the book.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0393
clientTexts.value: Hey! You are just in time. Our expedition's come to a halt thanks to all the Prinkers. Could you clear the way for us?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0368
clientTexts.value: A ways up from here lives a beastie called Red Toadrin... They are wicked little buggers, rather clever, and they frequently steal our stuff. Would you capture 40 of them and deliver them to Jano?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0369
clientTexts.value: Whoa, hey, the chief told me the whole story. You're a real pro, I can't believe you've caught this many already. Head on over to the expedition leader, he's waiting for you.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0370
clientTexts.value: Wow? You're already done with that? Lasa wasn't joking about your extraordinary abilities! Thank you kindly. I sent the notice from Ryan. Now go and find what you want.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0371
clientTexts.value: Uhh... Sorry about earlier. We've been isolated out here for a long time, so seeing a stranger was a real shock. Anyway, here's the clues you're after... In point of fact, it's Harmonin's journal. And I'm letting you have it as an apology.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0372
clientTexts.value: I've just been holding onto this book because no one can understand it, but you actually are able to use it. I hope you can get valuable information from it.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0373
clientTexts.value: Wow, Shaduwar! How cool is this!? ...Geez, don't tell me you're too cool to be excited about being on the new continent. You've only been here a few hours longer than I have!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0374
clientTexts.value: But...what is THIS? How thick it is! It's Harmonin's journal on the native peoples of Shaduwar? Huh... "I think these people are highly intelligent... I would use this as a pot rack."

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0375
clientTexts.value: Good to finally see you, how have you been? I was so thrilled to hear that you would come here as a representative of New Continent Exploration. They've named me the expedition leader, so I cannot be still. That's why I followed you in such a rush.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0376
clientTexts.value: The sage has already joined the research team. Come to think of it, I had a messenger deliver the book I got from Captain Teshar to him, but I haven't heard back. Can you check on it, Warrior?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0377
clientTexts.value: Heh... I forsaw you would visit me now. It's been a while. So, you've found another journal of Shaduwar? I cannot stop admiring your ability. Where in the world did you find this?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0378
clientTexts.value: Tsk... The translation will have to wait. My pen nib has broken, so I cannot copy anything down. I am sorry, but please get me some metal fragments from the monsters nearby. That would work for now.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0379
clientTexts.value: Ohh! Thanks a lot, this is excellent! I will make you a translated book as soon as possible. I feel so excited to transcribe such a splendid text! It is great to be here. Thanks, Warrior.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0380
clientTexts.value: What? Unbelievable! The last page of the journal is blank... Touch here, this part. Doesn't it feel different from the other pages? It's as if it doesn't want to show this part to anyone...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0381
clientTexts.value: However, considering the surrounding text, the page did not used to be blank. It must be ensorceled. In this situation, I can remove the spell with a sprinkle of Lere Powder... Unfortunately, I do not have any on hand.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0382
clientTexts.value: Can you go to Magician and get some Lere Powder? A mage also came along with us. Go and ask her.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0383
clientTexts.value: Well met! Lere Powder? A simple request. I can make it from Hatsalah resin. It takes only a moment once I have the materials. If you would like some Lere Powder, go over there and capture a Hatsalah now!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0385
clientTexts.value: Yes, this is a Hatsalah. Hold a moment, and I will prepare your Lere Powder. You have a good eye to find a Hatsalah. They can be quite confusing, you see.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0386
clientTexts.value: ...Huh? Did you hear that? —There's smoke coming from the direction of the camp! Let's go!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0387
clientTexts.value: It's awful! Yeti just invaded and kidnapped the children... You there, I will reward you if you save them. Please... Please save our children!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0390
clientTexts.value: You are here just in time. I was just thinking about how to handle all the Prinkers roaming around here. Now I can focus on my work, thanks to you.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0384
clientTexts.value: Oh dear... No, this will not work. This is a Jr. Hatsalah. Very similar, but different. This one is too young for its resin to be effective. I need the bigger ones for my material. Do not make a mistake this time.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0388
clientTexts.value: Thank you...thank you so much. Thanks to you, most of the children could come home safely. Some are still missing, but I know we'll find them soon. Here is the reward I promised. Take this.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0389
clientTexts.value: Did you save the native children? Good job. Now, this is the completed Lere Powder. Know that you are very lucky! There aren't many mages who know how to produce Lere Powder, even in Madrigal.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0392
clientTexts.value: Thank you. I've just finished the translation. Now, I am fairly certain that this is not the last volume. The story breaks off abruptly, you see. So it stands to reason that there are more stories that follow. And the one that's hidden must be quite impor

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0394
clientTexts.value: Thanks, the Prinkers are thinking twice before bothering us, now. It's much more managable. You know, I wonder why Prinkers are all the way out here? They're such small monsters out on Madrigal.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0395
clientTexts.value: Honestly, I think these skirmishes are going to continue until that Giant Prinker is defeated. Warrior, I know it is difficult, but please defeat the Giant Prinker as well. That should get the Prinkers back under control.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0396
clientTexts.value: Thank you. Now, we can get relieved. If the Head is killed, the rest will run away because of Prinker's nature. Fortunately, Prinkers, here, have the same nature.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0397
clientTexts.value: Here's the book from the sage...whoof! It's so heavy! How in the world can he hold it with just one hand? Anyway... Hmm...interesting... Ah! There's some techniques to take out monsters in here. Lucky!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0398
clientTexts.value: I know you're tired, but we can't rest just yet. Apparently, there are a bunch of Crohells headed this way. We should take them out as soon as possible, or who knows what they'll do to the camp.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0399
clientTexts.value: Great work, but it'll only get tougher from here. Since we hunted down so many Jr. Crohells, their parents will be coming after us. Mothers are much bigger and fiercer than juniors. Stay on your guard.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0400
clientTexts.value: Yes, I heard the story from the natives. I sent out scouts a few hours ago, just in case. They should be heading back now.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0401
clientTexts.value: Oh, here come the scouts. ...Hmm? ...Just as I thought, a swarm of Crohell are coming here. We will lead this time.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0402
clientTexts.value: With the tips in that book, I think we'll be much more effective fighting the monsters in this area. Warrior, can you take care of the Crohells coming from the center of the lake? We all appreciate it!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0403
clientTexts.value: Great work, Warrior. But...there is another problem. The remaining Crohells have occupied the lake, which is where the natives get their drinking water. If we leave them like this, the whole settlement will die from thirst.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0404
clientTexts.value: You know... The Crohells' movements are awfully strategic. Taking over a lake is what a military force would do. Someone's got to be controlling the Crohells.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0405
clientTexts.value: Whoof, these monsters are super strong, aren't they? I guess that's how it is on the New Continent... Anyway, they're the perfect targets for us Kyon Soldiers! I mean, yeah, it's tough, but tough jobs are what we are for. Isn't it right?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0431
clientTexts.value: What? You cannot see me even though I saved you!? And it was so tough to fly here, you are too mean.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0432
clientTexts.value: Oh, good job. While you were fighting, I looked around the cabin with Teshar, and we found something totally unexpected.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0433
clientTexts.value: It's Harmonin's will. There are a lot of stories about his later years, but it seems he quietly passed away in his beloved continent. Let me take a look at this...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0486
clientTexts.value: Unbelievable! The Altar of Sun became the seat of evil!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0406
clientTexts.value: Hey, I have something to tell you. So, I encountered a giant monster wreathed in blue flames while going through the Cursed Aminus Dungeon a few month ago. It looked like the incarnation of flame.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0407
clientTexts.value: The monster perched in the middle of a magic circle, but was surrounded by prone and bleeding children... They must have been sacrifices.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0408
clientTexts.value: Frightened, I ran away...but after you started talking about missing kids... I think what I saw was meant to resurrect Astaroth.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0409
clientTexts.value: As far as I know, the only Masquerpet who could do that with a human's life is Kumi. She is the boss of the Cursed Aminus Dungeon, and called the Queen of Blood.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0410
clientTexts.value: I will help you this time since you saved our children. Now it's our turn. Please let us save the remaining children.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0411
clientTexts.value: O-o-oh man, I just saw a nine-tailed fox! Rukas warned me, but I didn't believe him... Ugh, now I've got the heebie-jeebies!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0412
clientTexts.value: According to your story, Astaroth must have flown from here to Madrigal. The children must have been dragged here without a clue, and sacrificed for Astaroth's resurrection... It's heartbreaking.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0413
clientTexts.value: But I am relieved that we can prevent even bigger sacrifices thanks to you. Don't be too depressed. Now, this is a reward from our mercenaries. Thank you so much. Take a good rest. Tomorrow is another day.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0414
clientTexts.value: Thank you. As expected, the monsters here seem to be controlled by Kumi. Fortunately, we used the attack strategy written in the journal and kept damage to a minimum.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0415
clientTexts.value: Ah, come to think of it, I saw a strange box during our research. None of our equipment could get it to budge. Is there any possibility that one of the natives could open it?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0416
clientTexts.value: Mr. Vespu might know how to open it, but that's not much help. While you were fighting Kumi, he got attacked trying to save the remaining children.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0417
clientTexts.value: He's not quite on death's door, but you cannot see him until he is well.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0418
clientTexts.value: Can you go to Eastia Canyon and show this note to Old Man Luca? You can take a portal to Eastia Canyon in the northern valley.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0419
clientTexts.value: Oh, you are here. As a matter of fact, I was in hurry to come back here after I was told about Vespu's accident. Can you come back a bit later? I am opening the portal now.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0420
clientTexts.value: Good timing. I just managed to finish this. Please be safe. You still have a lot of work to do.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0421
clientTexts.value: Heavens, where did you come from!? How could someone have made such a treacherous journey?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0422
clientTexts.value: What? Vespu got seriously hurt? Tsk, of course, he always rushes into things without thinking. He's infuriating...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0423
clientTexts.value: That man, what a constant bother! Unfortunately, I cannot let him die. Come on, you, I'll need you to help me help him.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0424
clientTexts.value: Hey, what is that wound? Oh dear, come here first. How did you get this? And not even saying a word about it? Do you want to be like Vespu?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0425
clientTexts.value: You should not abuse your youth, it only comes once. Drink this medicine. It tastes awful but is good for your health.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0426
clientTexts.value: Did you drink it all? Good. Now, let's go gather herbs. We only need a few.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0427
clientTexts.value: I wonder what's up with the Mosbis today. Herbs are important, but not getting hurt is even more important! There should be a shelter after a short climb. Let's go there.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0428
clientTexts.value: I honestly don't understand why monsters are attacking so much. Don't tell me I look tasty! You must be attracting them, young'un; I am mostly gristle!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0429
clientTexts.value: Again with the monsters! Hey stripling, hurry up! The shelter is around the corner. You won't stand a chance if you get caught out here.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0430
clientTexts.value: Warrior, are you alright? No injuries? We rushed over here since we were worried about you, but seems like there was no need. I am so relieved you are safe.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0434
clientTexts.value: Right, this is Harmonin's will and also the proof of his life. He did many great things. Oh right, come to think of it, a historian here found a clue in this box. Why don't you go and see him?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0435
clientTexts.value: Ah, you made it. Let me begin... Most of us here in the camp are descendants of members of Harmonin's expedition team. So, people here keep at least one object from their ancestors in their caravans.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0436
clientTexts.value: The Star and Sun is the symbolic pattern of the Shaduwar Exploration Team. I studied what your expedition leader found; it is a box where the exploration team's documents were kept.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0437
clientTexts.value: If you try to open this box by force, everything in there will be completely destroyed in an instant. That is why few know about this box.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0438
clientTexts.value: According to the will the sage found, the box should be at the northern camping site. I believe Masquerpets may have stolen the box to dig into secrets of the Shaduwar Expedition Team.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0439
clientTexts.value: Let's go! Please take good care of the historian.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0440
clientTexts.value: Good heavens, what are these? Even I've never seen monsters like these before! Look, we should hurry. Follow me at all costs!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0441
clientTexts.value: Oh...oh my goodness... This...this is the altar of light! It's so different from how the books described it... I am terrified!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0442
clientTexts.value: Seems like this is no place to take a peaceful walk. I feel something off here... Plus, there's all the monsters, this place is very dangerous. Warrior! Expedition Leader! You both be careful!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0443
clientTexts.value: There's no end to them... Don't let them surround us!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0445
clientTexts.value: Oh my dear! Miss Teshar! Warrior, this won't work. We should retreat to a safer place.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0446
clientTexts.value: Phew! Even teleportation is tiring. Miss Teshar...? Oh! What's wrong? Wake up!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0447
