clientTexts.value: Urgh... We need to evacuate Teshar to the camping site or Flaris as soon as possible. Otherwise, it will be bad.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0448
clientTexts.value: Don't do anything reckless while I am not here. Mercenary had the same expression as you before he made a mess.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0449
clientTexts.value: Hmm, I will give you this necklace. I put a defensive spell on it. So long as you're wearing it, it should protect you. Hold on, I will put on another protection spell, too.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0450
clientTexts.value: That should do it. Don't overdo it and get in over your head. If you die, I will make you into a zombie slave!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0451
clientTexts.value: Hmm.. It should be somewhere around here... Here it is! Warrior! You found the Key of Star.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0452
clientTexts.value: I heard it from the magician. You entered the magic circle alone, without any sort of plan like an idiot. I was really worried about you so I rushed over here... Thank goodness you're safe.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0453
clientTexts.value: Don't go off on your own next time, alright? Yes, you're strong, but that doesn't mean you're not going to run into trouble that's even stronger.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0454
clientTexts.value: What? You saw a human-like Masquerpet? Perhaps...that kid used to be human before becoming a Masquerpet.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0455
clientTexts.value: We came across cases like that before... Mostly happens when a dead person's strong will or evil magic combines with rifts in nature.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0456
clientTexts.value: The Masquerpet Luna may have been a kid who was kidnapped and killed. It's terrible that children are suffering like this when they should be able to live in peace.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0457
clientTexts.value: Fufufu... So we meet again, my dear enemy. I see your face is as dumb as always.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0458
clientTexts.value: You are not confusing me with that worthless scoundrel Astaroth, are you? ...Hmph, so you really don't know who I am.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0459
clientTexts.value: No matter, you will find that out in time. I heard that you defeated Kumi. I should thank you for killing that bothersome fox.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0461
clientTexts.value: Hey! Warrior! Get ahold of yourself, don't close your eyes! Here, take this HP potion and recover!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0460
clientTexts.value: As a token of gratitude, I shall present you with this gift. Just take a few deep breaths, and you'll be able to have a nice, long nap. I think you humans call it...toxic fog. Hee hee hee...hahahaha!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0462
clientTexts.value: If you don't pull yourself together fast, you're as good as dead! Don't tell me you're ready to meet Rhisis at your age, young'un! If not, take the potion and wake up!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0463
clientTexts.value: If you won't act, then who will? You need to find the source of this toxic fog before it covers the whole world!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0464
clientTexts.value: Oho? You look confused. I'll make it simple... When you're beautiful, anything is possible. Hahaha~ Now, get out of here. I'll take the child, never you mind the rest.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0465
clientTexts.value: Hey, you! Warrior! You are safe! I am so relieved.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0466
clientTexts.value: A girl in a robe appeared and said you were poisoned by toxic fog, and then just disappeared. I was worried sick! So I'm glad to see you are okay.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0467
clientTexts.value: Warrior, you look pale. Old Man Luca made an antidote for you, here. Don't worry, he added some strawberry flavor so it should taste good.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0468
clientTexts.value: I just rushed to be here after I heard that Lasa had disappeared from the camp site during the treatment. I found Lasa on my way here, but I was worried about you. ...Right, Mercenary is looking for you. You should go now.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0469
clientTexts.value: Good to see you again. It is nice to have one positive thing in this land of monsters and air pollution...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0470
clientTexts.value: I heard the story from Magician and Acrobat. Once you're ready, let's go find the altar of Sun. Don't take everything on your shoulders, and you should trust your colleagues sometimes.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0471
clientTexts.value: The deeper we go into the valley, the thicker the toxic fog becomes! It would be a big problem if Luca had not make that antidote.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0472
clientTexts.value: I used to play here as a kid, and now it's a monster's nest... My memories are literally being destroyed by Masquerpets. It's heartbreaking.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0473
clientTexts.value: The toxic fog is getting thicker. If we don't do anything about this, I think the toxic fog will reach the Shaduwar campsite beyond the portal.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0474
clientTexts.value: Mercenary's right, but I think it is still lucky. Thicker fog means we are closer to our destination. Let's keep searching!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0475
clientTexts.value: You're still so energetic after such a fierce attack? You're really something!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0476
clientTexts.value: I've lived here my whole life. This is the first time I've ever heard anything about toxic fog, much less about it spreading throughout the continent.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0477
clientTexts.value: Phew... Think I'm finally finished with cleanup around here. ...Oh, I almost forgot. I've got something for you!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0478
clientTexts.value: This is from my late father… It's called shining ori...kallum? Talcum? Something like that... Of course, as you know, I don't know how to use it.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0479
clientTexts.value: I researched some old documents, but they only said it is an ore to upgrade an item, and there was nothing further. I don't even know what "upgrade" is. Well, hopefully you have better luck than I did!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0480
clientTexts.value: Please use it well. But I'm not worried... I think you can use that more effectively than anyone.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0481
clientTexts.value: Wow, this must be shining Orichalcum! You are so lucky you can get an upgrade item like this in these dangerous days.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0482
clientTexts.value: As you know, you can upgrade an item up to a higher level with this shining Orichalcum. It is perfect for a dangerous place where who knows what could pop out of any corner.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0483
clientTexts.value: Now, let's get out there and find the source of this toxic fog. If we spend any more time dilly-dallying, who knows what terrible things could happen.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0484
clientTexts.value: Found it! Over there! A massive amount of evil energy is coming from there!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0485
clientTexts.value: Yeah, that has got to be the source of it. The evil miasma is so thick I can barely breathe... Stay strong, or we could be overtaken!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0487
clientTexts.value: Ugh... The evil is too strong, we have to retreat. Otherwise, we all lose our lives. I will teleport us to the northern camping site! Stay close to me.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0488
clientTexts.value: Hrgh... In all my life, I've never felt such a terrible evil. Just being that close was terrifying.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0489
clientTexts.value: It was sudden, but Magician made a good decision. Just as she said, we would have died if we had stayed at that altar any longer.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0490
clientTexts.value: I am relieved that we are all safe, but now we are really far from the Dreadful Cave. I can't believe that we need this much distance to be safe. What a powerful evil...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0491
clientTexts.value: Still, if we can't get close, it's a big problem. I can't believe there is nothing we can do.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0492
clientTexts.value: After researching the climate and the environment of this area, I've found that the toxic fog is artificially created by someone. Probably it's a Masquerpet that's behind this.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0493
clientTexts.value: But with our current numbers and equipment, there's no way we can resolve this. Even Magician's magic isn't enough in this situation. I'm really worried.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0494
clientTexts.value: Well, let's take a rest for now, heaven knows we deserve it. Just because you take everything on your shoulders doesn'tm ean you don't have to put it down sometimes.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0495
clientTexts.value: Yes, in this short time you've done as many feats as the warriors of old. That said, I am still worried. Please listen to this old man, alright?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0496
clientTexts.value: What? Why are you here? I know you are worried but sometimes you need to take care of yourself. Do not overestimate the effects of potions and magic.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0497
clientTexts.value: Sure, they work fine when you're healthy. But if you're not well, even the best potion or strongest spell won't be able to help you. Take care of yourself.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0498
clientTexts.value: There is a way. Poison is poison, and antidote is antidote. Simply speaking, if you lose some strength, you can supplement it with magic, antidotes, or potions. That will certainly help.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0499
clientTexts.value: I think you already heard from Acrobat. Actually, there is no way other than this. The sage knows the reaction for sure. That's why he advised us to stop.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0500
clientTexts.value: In the end, fighting is going to be the most efficient way. Having a mix of long distance, mid-range, and melee attacks will keep things quick.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0501
clientTexts.value: Don't worry, our forces will go with you. That will be more effective than you fighting alone. Are you in?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0502
clientTexts.value: ...Yes, you are a heavenly warrior. Okay, Mercenary! Acrobat! Let's go. It's time for revenge!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0503
clientTexts.value: You joined this reckless operation because of me. I am sorry.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0504
clientTexts.value: Fine... I understand other people can do this, but Acrobat is also in! This is reckless, just like old times. Nothing changed...

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0505
clientTexts.value: I respect your courage to stand against danger. But you should know there is a line between courage and stubbornness. Don't be pressured into the latter just because you're a warrior.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0506
clientTexts.value: But from your expression...I think you will go through with this anyhow. So this once I won't stop you. But be careful. Finding the Key of the Sun is important, but it's not more important than your life.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0507
clientTexts.value: You are the last hope for this world. Never forget the difference between courage and stubbornness. ...Good luck to you.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0508
clientTexts.value: Hey there! Yahoo, we meet again! I see you've gotten stronger, you were just so weak before, like a little baby! Or is it that my potion worked that well? Hahaha!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0509
clientTexts.value: I hope that training was worthwhile! Ah, I see you've come up with another reckless operation. Lucky for you, this delicate, youthful flower will prepare a great spell for you!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0510
clientTexts.value: You ready? I'm sending you to the entrance of the Dreadful Cave. Poison for poison, antidote for antidote? Nonsense. How about flying away from the poison? Anyhoo, good luck, Warrior!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0511
clientTexts.value: I am so relieved that you survived such a reckless operation. By the way, who is that? Where did you find that kid?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0512
clientTexts.value: I cannot believe this, it really exists... I've dreamt of this, it's Harmonin's last journal. And even though it's ensorceled, I have enough Lere Powder that it won't take very long to translate it at all.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0513
clientTexts.value: Oh, are you looking for me? You've got more sense than I thought, I'll have to revise my opinion of you, hee hee. Here, I'll give you a good gift. Show this to your sage, tell him you stumbled across it on your way to him. It will be so funny.

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0514
clientTexts.value: I was worried since you disappeared without saying anything. Was there something wrong? What is that in your hand?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0515
clientTexts.value: Oh, Warrior. Long time no see. Did you find the Shaduwar Continent? I've heard rumors about all the adventurers! ...What? You have something to show me?

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0516
clientTexts.value: Wow, look at this! This is a thorned scale from a Meteonyker! There are dragons in Shaduwar!? Goodness gracious, Meteonyker! What a situation!

clientTexts.name: COMPDIAL_NAME_0517
clientTexts.value: Knowing that Meteonykers are in the new continent, we cannot head out half-cocked. Those beasts are no joke; I am not sure we can survive even we are prepared for war. Better to prepare for death.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00001
clientTexts.value: Where should I look for allies?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00002
clientTexts.value: There is something called companionship. After going through many battles, you will find allies you can depend on.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00003
clientTexts.value: I see. I hope I can find dependable allies!

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00004
clientTexts.value: Agreed. And more than just seeking out good allies, try to become a good ally yourself.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00005
clientTexts.value: How far should I follow this road?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00006
clientTexts.value: Not that far... Say hello to Captain Teshar.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00007
clientTexts.value: I will. Thanks for letting me know!

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00010
clientTexts.value: All equipment has its own limited stats which improve your strength. We divide those limited stats into separate grades, which we call "tiers."

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00011
clientTexts.value: So that means that higher tiers have higher max stats...which means it'll improve my strength that much more?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00012
clientTexts.value: Yes. Even if two pieces of equipment share the same name or monetary value, their stats will be different based on their tier. High tiers mean better stats.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00013
clientTexts.value: Understood. I will do my best to get high-tier equipment.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00014
clientTexts.value: What should I know before entering La Christiana?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00015
clientTexts.value: All I know is that once it showed up, a bunch of Masquerpets appeared, and children went missing.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00016
clientTexts.value: If so, before more children go missing, I will find out what is going on with La Christiana.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00017
clientTexts.value: Why are the children being kidnapped?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00018
clientTexts.value: Do you have any other information?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00021
clientTexts.value: Oh! There is a way to get more information.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00022
clientTexts.value: No... May I ask you something?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00023
clientTexts.value: Go ahead. How can I refuse a question from my savior?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00024
clientTexts.value: Have you seen Nomierr? I'm looking for him... I heard he went to the Hillid Mountains.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00025
clientTexts.value: Hm... I don't know about Nomierr, but I'd stay away from the Hillid Mountains.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00027
clientTexts.value: Oh yeah, it was super creepy. Nothing about it was normal at all.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00028
clientTexts.value: Do you know where he headed?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00029
clientTexts.value: No. I don't know where he was headed...

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00030
clientTexts.value: But, Nomierr was going down this road, towards the Hillid Mountains. You might be able to catch up with him if you go this way.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00032
clientTexts.value: Hm.. I don't have much information about them, but I've heard they are extremely expensive.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00033
clientTexts.value: Why would people go after them without knowing what they were?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00034
clientTexts.value: Money? Greed isn't the best thing for good judgment. People heard the minerals were worth a lot, and didn't care about the rest.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00037
clientTexts.value: How did you survive when the others died?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00038
clientTexts.value: The others knew about combat, but I only knew about minerals. I'm ashamed to admit it, but when they fought the Masquerpets, I ran for it.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00039
clientTexts.value: Shameful or not, sounds like that was the right thing to do.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00040
clientTexts.value: I agree. A little longer and he would have surely been killed by Masquerpets.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00041
clientTexts.value: It was definitely dangerous. We had to pay attention not only to the Masquerpets, but to the geographical condition, too.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00042
clientTexts.value: Yes. I understand. Do you have any other information?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00043
clientTexts.value: Hm... I can't think of anything. He headed to the Hillid Mountains. I could barely see him.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00044
clientTexts.value: I understand. I'll see if people near the Hillid Mountains know anything, and start searching.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00046
clientTexts.value: I will. I will let him know you are looking for him too.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00048
clientTexts.value: Ha ha ha... Wouldn't you like to know...

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00049
clientTexts.value: ...You are not Nomierr! You pretended to be him, but are really helping the Masquerpets!

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00050
clientTexts.value: Haha! And what is wrong with helping Masquerpets?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00052
clientTexts.value: You will understand soon... Put your weapon away...

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00054
clientTexts.value: You..? Who are you? Why am I here?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00056
clientTexts.value: Ah? Now I remember... I helped Masquerpets...to kidnap...children?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00058
clientTexts.value: Yoon was said to be even more powerful than Astaroth.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00059
clientTexts.value: Aren't we in trouble if Yoon is that powerful?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00060
clientTexts.value: He WAS that powerful, but who knows about now. Yoon was sealed for a long time.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00061
clientTexts.value: I was too late... If only I'd gone more quickly...

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00062
clientTexts.value: You did your best. It's not your fault. Don't blame yourself.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00064
clientTexts.value: It's impressive... That's why Astaroth summoned him.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00065
clientTexts.value: Yes. Because of his ability, they can easily kidnap more children.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00066
clientTexts.value: It will get worse as time goes by.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00067
clientTexts.value: Yes. That's why we are investigating his ability.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00068
clientTexts.value: What? You just summoned him. Now you want me to kill him?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00069
clientTexts.value: Your job is not to question, it is to follow my orders.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00070
clientTexts.value: Oh! Interesting! You are up to something!

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00071
clientTexts.value: How about that? Do you like my offer?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00072
clientTexts.value: Did you think I would accept that offer? I'm fine on my own.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00073
clientTexts.value: Damn it! Astaroth knew my plan..

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00074
clientTexts.value: Haha... Just as I expected. You are still the idiotic Yoon that I remember.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00075
clientTexts.value: Do you think I'm stupid enough to be fooled by you again!?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00076
clientTexts.value: Fuhuhu... Do you honestly think you can kill me in your current condition? Fool! Just become part of me!

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00077
clientTexts.value: Hm... There are many quests about killing Masquerpets.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00078
clientTexts.value: Is this related to the kidnappings?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00079
clientTexts.value: Yes. Someone leaked the information to the parents who lost their children.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00080
clientTexts.value: Then the clients must be the parents.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00081
clientTexts.value: Yes, that is correct. However, killing low-level Masquerpets isn't going to do anything to help.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00082
clientTexts.value: Can we explain, or give them advice?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00083
clientTexts.value: These aren't good rumors to spread.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00084
clientTexts.value: I know. But we can't do anything in this situation.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00085
clientTexts.value: Why? We could just say that the rumor is wrong.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00086
clientTexts.value: It's not that simple. They got evidence from their missing children...scraps of their clothing and the like.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00089
clientTexts.value: Are you talking about the missing children?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00090
clientTexts.value: Yes, I have heard that rumor.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00092
clientTexts.value: Not sure... What are your thoughts?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00093
clientTexts.value: There's speculation that the rumor was started by the Masquerpet Astaroth. I agree.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00094
clientTexts.value: Astaroth... I've been thinking the same thing.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00095
clientTexts.value: Any info on where they're headed?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00096
clientTexts.value: No... However, we got descriptions of the Masquerpets who took the rest of the children.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00097
clientTexts.value: I think we got fooled by Astaroth.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00099
clientTexts.value: He divided the children, and used the rest as bait to shift our attention.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00100
clientTexts.value: Then, where are the rest of the children?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00101
clientTexts.value: Maybe they're heading to Astaroth while we are here fooled.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00102
clientTexts.value: I'm sorry we couldn't find all of the children.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00103
clientTexts.value: If we want to be able to hold our own with the Masquerpets, we need to prepare higher-tier equipment.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00105
clientTexts.value: Fusing three of the same part, tier, and grade will raise the equipment's tier by one.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00106
clientTexts.value: Oh, so we want to collect as much equipment as possible!

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00107
clientTexts.value: Anyone can get the gear they're looking for at the Auction House in the village.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00108
clientTexts.value: Can I buy good equipment at the Auction House?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00109
clientTexts.value: Of course. And you can get non-binding gold and non-binding diamond by selling equipment or items you have.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00111
clientTexts.value: Why don't you get a better weapon in the Auction House for this battle?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00112
clientTexts.value: Uh, are you a...h...human? You come from Ma..Madrigal Continent? Uh... He...here is Shaduwar Continent. Why are you here?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00113
clientTexts.value: Oh...hello. I am looking for an explorer named Harmonin. Do you know him?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00114
clientTexts.value: You're looking for someone called Harmonin? Huh...I've never heard of him. Why don't you go ask Uncle Ryan over there?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00115
clientTexts.value: Ohh, you're a new face. How strange, we had monsters flying on a ship the other day, and now, a human...

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00116
clientTexts.value: Hello, I am from Madrigal. A child, Lasa, told me to visit you. I heard you know the history of this area very well.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00117
clientTexts.value: Lasa sent you, huh? ...Sorry, but I don't know that I can believe all that. If you wanna talk, find the expedition leader. I haven't got anything to say to strangers.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00118
clientTexts.value: Hello. I came to find someone called Harmonin. Do you have a minute?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00119
clientTexts.value: Who are you? Are you from Madrigal? Really? Hahaha! That's sure a pleasant surprise! So, what brings you out here?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00120
clientTexts.value: In the name of the gods, I summon thee to wash away the sins of the cursed with your azure flame and forever vanquish your enemies... Lightning Storm!

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00121
clientTexts.value: A book I read when I was young led me to the world of exploration. I searched everywhere for the truth, and finally, I found the continent only mentioned in legends.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00122
clientTexts.value: And I found the legends in the new continent. Not just anybody, but I! The fairy tales handed down by our parents were true!

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00123
clientTexts.value: You, who reads this will, do you want the truth? Then find the keys hidden in the Altar of Light and the Altar of Sun. Then, open the Box of Sun and Star hidden in the northern campsite, and read what is within.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00124
clientTexts.value: That will be the important key that opens the future. Will-reader, descendants, I will happily await you who endure the truth in a place far away.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00125
clientTexts.value: Hey, I am sorry to say this, but I have to go. Vespu needs emergency treatment. Feel free to contact me anytime you need medicine.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00126
clientTexts.value: Unbreakable shield of the vanguard... I inherit your power and bravely fight in your honor as the spearhead of justice. Absolute Barrier!

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00127
clientTexts.value: Ta-dah! You have the pleasure of meeting the the most beautiful girl in Madrigal! Masqurpets that follow humans? So arrogant! Away with you!

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00128
clientTexts.value: Rrgh... Hah! I must congratulate you, human, it is rare that anyone can cause me this much trouble. But do not think that means you'll get the better of me... Rrrahhh!

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00129
clientTexts.value: !? You...you! How did you get here!?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00130
clientTexts.value: Tch! You breathe a word of this to anyone and you'll be no more than stardust! Don't tell me you're ready to meet the goddess Rhisis already, are you!?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00131
clientTexts.value: !? You...you! Rrghhh! How did you get here!?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00132
clientTexts.value: Ahhhhhh! Why! Why this!? Why! Are! You! Here!?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00133
clientTexts.value: Oh... That...that's enough! Don't you say a word! We are too young to go to Lady Rhisis!

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00134
clientTexts.value: (What's in the world is the matter with these people?)

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00135
clientTexts.value: Well... I brought her because she was crying alone in the Dreadful Cave. I think she may be one of the missing children.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00136
clientTexts.value: Oh... Poor kid. I can feel the weak spirit of a Masquerpet from her... We should look into it in more detail when we get back to the village. Now, open this box with the key you got.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00137
clientTexts.value: Well done. You have proved yourself to be brave enough to face the hidden truth. I am Harmonin, the explorer...true discoverer of Shaduwar.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00138
clientTexts.value: Hope transcends beyond race. I have set up a portal in the north for the one who will face the truth. As soon it's opened, you shall face the truth.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00139
clientTexts.value: A land nurtured by Mother Nature... And a society flourished there, one not unlike that of humans. We called them Therians.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00140
clientTexts.value: Brothers, descendants and my friends. My life will end here. But if there is someone who succeed me and someday take up my mantle, I can close my eyes with a happy smile.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00141
clientTexts.value: Let me see... Gosh! Where did you get this? What? You found it on the way here?

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00142
clientTexts.value: This is a Meteonyker thorny scale!!! Meteonyker, the strongest Masquerpet of the Genesis War, ages ago... I thought they were extinct!

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00143
clientTexts.value: No, it's too difficult to visit the Therians. I have to tell everybody about this now. If by any chance Meteonyker is near, all that's left for us is destruction.

clientTexts.name: DIALOG_NAME_00144
clientTexts.value: I will tell the people about this, take this Flaris Blink Wing. Return to the village, and show Mikyel the thorny scale. There is no time to waste.

clientTexts.name: INTRO_DESC_0001
clientTexts.value: There was once a time when life was precious.

clientTexts.name: INTRO_DESC_0002
clientTexts.value: Nobody knew the consequences of the small darkness in the world...

clientTexts.name: INTRO_DESC_0003
clientTexts.value: Rhisis, Goddess of the World, was stung by a thorn of loneliness.

clientTexts.name: INTRO_DESC_0004
clientTexts.value: Rhisis eventually created three godly beings: Bubble, Shade and Ivillis.

clientTexts.name: INTRO_DESC_0005
clientTexts.value: Shade, created from anger and rage, set about to destroy the world.

clientTexts.name: INTRO_DESC_0006
clientTexts.value: She built an army of Masquerpets to wipe out the people of Madrigal.

clientTexts.name: INTRO_DESC_0007
clientTexts.value: A great battle began between humans and Shade's Masquerpets.

clientTexts.name: INTRO_DESC_0008
clientTexts.value: Heroes stood up to Shade and sacrificed their lives to save Madrigal.

clientTexts.name: INTRO_DESC_0009
clientTexts.value: Ages passed and the people of Madrigal began to grow strong and thrive once again.

clientTexts.name: INTRO_DESC_0010
clientTexts.value: However, there is always a shadow behind the light...
